        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Wanted: Disgruntled Employees to Deploy Ransomware"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Krebsonsecurity recently posted an article about a tactic to deploy ransomware using someone from *within* an organization they are wanting to attack. Criminal cyber attackers try many ways to infiltrate a profitable enterprise to get a good return from a ransomware infection. One tactic that is causing concern is cyber attackers contacting employees directly and asking them to help unleash malware inside their employer’s network. These desperate cyber criminals offer the potential \"insider threat actors\" a percentage of any ransom they receive."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Cybercriminals have been known to use disgruntled employees to help them in their nefarious plans. For instance, there has been a threat of disgruntled employees creating identities on darknet sites (i.e. sites that can only be accessed with specific software, configurations, authorization and oftentimes used for both illegal and legitimate reasons), and then offering to trash their employer's network for a fee."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Several established ransomware affiliate gangs have recently started soliciting illicit access to corporate networks. For example, the Lockbit 2.0 ransomware-as-a-service gang includes a solicitation for insiders in the desktop wallpaper left behind on systems encrypted with the malware."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "To read the full article, please visit the following link:"
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "text": "https://krebsonsecurity.com/2021/08/wanted-disgruntled-employees-to-deploy-ransomware/",
          "url": "https://krebsonsecurity.com/2021/08/wanted-disgruntled-employees-to-deploy-ransomware/"
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "FEMA Offers Exercise Assistance to Stakeholders"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) is accepting requests for exercise support through the "
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "text": "National Exercise Program",
          "url": "https://www.fema.gov/emergency-managers/national-preparedness/exercises/nep"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": ". State, local, tribal, and territorial (SLTT) jurisdictions can request no-cost assistance for exercise design, development, conduct and evaluation to validate capabilities across all mission areas."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "FEMA is hosting webinars for all interested governments and other community partners on the exercise support process. Please visit the "
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "text": "webinar webpage",
          "url": "https://www.fema.gov/emergency-managers/national-preparedness/exercises/nep#webinars"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": " to register. The webinar dates are as follows:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "list_type": "unordered",
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "Webinar 1: 1 p.m. ET on Aug. 30."
            },
            {
              "text": "Webinar 2: 2 p.m. ET on Sept.7."
            },
            {
              "text": "Webinar 3: 3 p.m. ET on Sept. 15."
            },
            {
              "text": "Webinar 4: 4 p.m. ET on Sept. 23."
            },
            {
              "text": "Webinar 5: 1 p.m. ET on Oct. 1."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Fall 2021 requests for support are due no later than November 1. To submit a request for exercise support, download the "
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "text": "nomination",
          "url": "https://www.fema.gov/sites/default/files/documents/fema_nep-nomination-form.pdf"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": " form, then email the completed form with any supporting documentation to "
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "text": "NEP@fema.dhs.gov",
          "url": "mailto:NEP@fema.dhs.gov"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": ". Awardees will be notified by December 10. FEMA will hold additional exercise support rounds in the spring and fall of 2022. For questions, contact FEMA at "
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "text": "NEP@fema.dhs.gov",
          "url": "mailto:NEP@fema.dhs.gov"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "."
