        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 1,
          "text": "2021 N.C. Cybersecurity Awareness Symposium – October 6-7, 2021"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "October will be "
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "text": "National Cybersecurity Awareness Month (NCSAM)",
          "url": "National Cybersecurity Awareness Month (NCSAM)"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": ". The overarching theme will be “Do Your Part. #BeCyberSmart.” This theme encourages individuals and organizations to own their role in protecting their part of cyberspace, stressing personal accountability and the importance of taking proactive steps to enhance cybersecurity."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "In support of this national campaign, the N.C. Department of Information Technology (DIT) will be hosting a two-day virtual "
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "text": "N.C. Cybersecurity Awareness Symposium",
          "url": "N.C. Cybersecurity Awareness Symposium"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": " on October 6-7, 2021. This will be an opportunity for attendees to learn from cyber leaders and subject matter experts in the private, public and academic sectors on various topics related to maximizing cyber spend while protecting data and systems from compromise."
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Triangle InfoSeCon Virtual Conference October 28-29, 2021"
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "text": "Triangle InfoSeCon",
          "url": "Triangle InfoSeCon"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": " is the largest annual Information Security conference in the Triangle area and is the flagship event of the "
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "text": "Raleigh Chapter",
          "url": "Raleigh Chapter"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": " of the Information System Security Association (ISSA). This year’s event will be Thursday October 28 and Friday October 29."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "The chapter holds training events during their monthly meetings and provides an annual Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP) review. As an organization, they believe that Information Security is both the present and the future, and it is incumbent upon cybersecurity professionals to try to influence the decision makers of today and to train the security leaders of tomorrow. In addition to several cybersecurity presentations, the "
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "text": "Triangle InfoSeCon",
          "url": "Triangle InfoSeCon"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": " event will host an IT Leadership Forum and a Capture the Flag exercise."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "For more information and to register for this event, please visit "
        },
        {
          "type": "link",
          "text": "here",
          "url": "here"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "."
        },
